I got a bit tired of Midjourney's limited and buggy archive download solution so I decided to put together a quick and dirty chrome extension with GPT-4.

Features:
- Select a date range which you want to download images from
- Only downloads upscaled images (no more cleaning up grids)
- Option to download all v5+ and niji 5+ grid images separated
- Each download contains a `archived_jobs.json` file that contains all metadata about the jobs including prompts (can also be downloaded separately)
- Batch download support for older devices

Make sure you're logged into Midjourney, otherwise this won't work.
